ls0 ws0">temple, and the rebuilding of the altar, after Judas Maccabeus had </div><div class="t m7ef x27 h28 y1964 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">driven out the Syrians in B. c. 164, was held in the ninth month. </div><div class="t m164d x11 h28 y1965 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">As Jesus desired to be present at the latter (John Jo : </div><div class="t mf5 x57 h2b y17fc ff4 fs10 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">22, </div><div class="t m412 x8d h28 y17fc ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">23), He </div><div class="t mdbb x11 h28 y1362 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">did not return to Galilee, but spent the intervening time in Judea. </div><div class="t m6ab x11 h28 y1ee4 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">His time was getting very short, and as little labor had been </div><div class="t m1145 x11 h28 y1d62 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bestowed upon Judea during His ministry, He therefore organized </div><div class="t m275 x11 h28 y19eb ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the large force of seventy disciples to go before Him to the various </div><div class="t m371 x11 h28 y21f4 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">towns as heralds of His approach. In this way, the people would </div><div class="t m1cb x11 h28 y1ade ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">be prepared for His coming, and much more could be accom-</div><div class="t md25 x11 h28 y6ba ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">plished in the short time left for His earthly ministry. This is a </div><div class="t m267 x11 h28 y1a31 ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">significant fact, and• one that should influence our actions, the </div><div class="t m191a x11 h28 y166a ff4 fs14 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">nearer the end draws on. </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
